                "paragraphs":  [
                                   "Naima Ibrahim Joo is an AI researcher and ICT educator with over 10 years of teaching experience at engineering institutions in Pakistan. She holds an MS in Computer Science with a specialisation in Artificial Intelligence from the National University of Technology (NUTECH), Islamabad, and is actively pursuing a PhD scholarship in Europe in the field of LLM Privacy and Security.",
                                   "She currently serves as a Voluntary Research Assistant under Dr. Syed Tahir Ali Shah, PhD Researcher at the University of Aveiro, Portugal, contributing to research on Human Factor in IoT â€” Emotion-Aware and Physiology-Aware Mobility Systems. Her contributions include systematic gap analysis across 11 peer-reviewed papers, identification of a novel research gap in real-time multimodal physiological safety monitoring for e-scooters, and supporting journal-level manuscript preparation.",
                                   "Her research interests focus on privacy-utility trade-offs in Differentially Private federated fine-tuning of Large Language Models, adversarial gradient manipulation, and secure aggregation in distributed AI systems. She is committed to translating advanced AI research into trustworthy, human-centred systems that benefit diverse communities."
                               ]
            },
